[Student "S"]
{NORTH, with a 5-card AND a 4-card Major first uses Stayman.

SOUTH denies a 4-card Major, so NORTH realizes that \Ss are out. 
He then bids \Hs, promising five of them.

SOUTH not only has three \Hs, she also has 17 points so 
she bids 4\H.}

